# SentinelAI Frontend - Cursor Rules

## Project context
- Next.js 16 App Router, React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS 4
- AI video intelligence / security monitoring SaaS
- Mock data in lib/api/; backend integration via apiFetch when ready

## Code organization
- app/ - Pages and app-specific components
- app/components/ - Reusable UI (Header, icons, landing/, dashboard/)
- hooks/ - Data hooks (useAlerts, useFootageSearch, etc.)
- lib/api/ - API layer (client, alerts, footage, analytics, monitoring)
- lib/ - types.ts, constants.ts
- docs/ - ARCHITECTURE, API, COMPONENTS, CONTRIBUTING

## Conventions
- Use JSDoc for exported functions and components
- Follow existing patterns in lib/api for new endpoints
- Add sessionId parameter to API calls for future backend
- Prefer hooks over inline fetch in components
- Use "use client" only when component needs interactivity

## Import aliases
- @/ maps to project root (e.g. @/lib/api, @/hooks)
